column168: XPO Logistics terminal XFO experienced a UN3082 Caromax 28 release from a 275-gallon poly tote. ERTS dispatched contractors to conduct cleanup operations. Contractors arrived onsite and confirmed approximately 2-gallons of product released to a 3’ x 2’ area of the wooden trailer floor and a 1’ x 1’ area of the concrete dock floor due to a crack in the top corner of the tote. The material was transferred from the damaged tote into a new one. Absorbents were deployed and worked into the impacted areas. The damaged tote was then cut up and containerized along with all impacted absorbents into (2) 55- gallon poly drums. The waste was staged onsite for terminal personnel to manage.

column168: On February 1, 2024, one (1) 330-gallon tote of UN3082 was punctured by a forklift and released approximately thirty (30) gallons of product to the dock floor. R+L Carriers retained Cura Emergency Services, LC who dispatched a crew from First Call Environmental (FCE) to remediate the impacted site.  FCE personnel deployed granular absorbents to the UN3082-impacted dock floor and swept them in with hand tools. Crews observed that they would not be able to lift the tote for a gravity feed and instead did a bucket transfer of all the remaining contents into an additional 330-gallon tote. All spent absorbents, clean up debris, and cut up 330-gallon tote were collected and containerized into five (5) 55-gallon drums for terminal disposal.

column168: On 2/12/2024, I john Vergis Hazardous Materials Officer for the WLE, was called by the WLE Car Shop Manager @0730 hrs. about tank car UTLX 205661 leaking in the WLE Rook Yard.  When I arrived to look at the car, I could see that is was leaking product from the protective housing on top the car.  I got on top the car and removed seal number 451443 from the protective housing cover and noticed that product was leaking from the Sample Line Valve.   Product was leaking from the valve plug.  I checked to see of the valve handle was shut and it was not tight.  I turned the valve handle one complete turn before it was shut tight.  I then checked to see if the valve plug was loose and when I touched the plug, it fell out.  I installed new thread sealant on the plug and installed it in the valve and tightened it tool tight.  I then cleaned off the top and sides of the car the best I could.  I installed new seal number 0000225 on the protective housing lid and then released the car back into transportation.
column169: Better car securement procedures need followed.

column168: XPO Logistics terminal XKC experienced a release UN3266 Mainline Liquid 102 from a 250-gallon poly tote. Contractors arrived onsite and confirmed approximately 10-gallons of material released to a 12’ x 2’ area of the trailer floor and a 10’ x 10’ area of the concrete lot underneath the trailer due to a pinhole puncture. The material was transferred from the damaged tote into a new one. Citric acid solution and absorbents were then deployed and worked into the impacted areas to clean and neutralize the release. column168: XPO Logistics Terminal XSL contacted ERTS to report a spill that occurred on the dock in St. Louis, MO. The spill consisted of approximately 2-gallons of UN1268 Rikeizai SBS-A02, which was released from a 275-gallon metal tote due to a forklift blade damaging the lid. The shipper sent terminal personnel a replacement lid which was secured onto the tote by terminal personnel and the tote was shipped on.
